

ocamlbuild 

The following targets are built. 

ID.map -> ID.map.d      -- dependencies needed to define ID's key
ID.map.d -> ID.map.od   -- build dependencies

When we need a map's data we don't require the .map but the .map.od. This 
ensure that it can be queried correctly with get (we have all the maps 
included with w.includes). 

ID.map.od -> ID.uriset.d    -- dependencies needed to defined ID's uriset
ID.uriset.d -> ID.uriset.od -- build dependencies
ID.uriset.od -> ID.uriset   -- build the uriset

After ID.uriset.od is built the URI set of the map can be determined. We
have all the dependencies needed to build the URI set.

After the uri set is built we build each uri, via the following procedure

ID.map.od -> ID+URI.uri.d     -- dependencies needed to define URI of ID. 
ID+URI.uri.d -> ID+URI.uri.od -- build dependencies 
ID+URI.uri.od -> ID+URI.uri   -- generate the URI content 

The whole URI set of a map can be built with ID.uriset.o

ID.uriset -> ID.uriset.o

The URI set of a map and the URIs of the maps it depends on and 
recursively can be build with as follows 

ID.uriset.o -> ID.site -- build recursive dependencies. 



Bugs
----

If you change a pathname it is not erased. 




